claims:
1. A method for improving the proliferative phase of a primary T Cell response in a mammal, comprising:
a. immunizing said mammal by administering a solution comprising an antigen capable of triggering a primary T Cell response in said mammal;
b. concurrently administering to said mammal a PPC composition obtained by heat extracting, at a temperature of about 80° C. or above, pine cones with a solution of potassium hydroxide;
